    "Captured by injecting Notion cookies obtained via Go SSO into a Playwright browser, then clicking the 'For personal life' onboarding option followed by 'Skip for now' on the desktop-app prompt. The /createSpace response does NOT contain a space_view record; the SPA invents a fresh space_view UUID client-side and then immediately POSTs /api/v3/saveTransactionsMain with a single transaction whose three operations (a) create the space_view, (b) listAfter it onto user_root.space_views, (c) keyedObjectListAfter it onto user_root.space_view_pointers. Only after this transaction does user_root.space_view_pointers become non-empty — which is what /loadUserContent + the proxy use to find the workspace.",
    "Go must NOT include domainType in the createSpace body (the SPA omits it).",
    "All UUIDs in transactions/requestId/space_view are client-generated; Notion accepts any well-formed UUID."
